reviewText: Amazing photgraphy. This was well done and very informative.
Anyone interested in Hummingbirds or nature in general will love this!

Up close shots of Hummingbirds! Stunning colors, shiny shimmering feathers in superb detail. I purchased this for the sole purpose of getting to see Hummingbirds up close and in Hi-Definition. I was NOT disappointed!!

A documentary covering some of the more recent findings in relation to these interesting birds including migration paths and how they fly and their penchant for eating insects and how they do so despite the handicap of specially shaped beaks to drink nectar. Being in high definition the myriad colours that these birds use are shown to good effect.
Bought for my wife for Christmas, she loves hummingbirds...and this DVD was very good.
Great documentary on an interesting subject with top-notch photography, though not QUITE as awesome as the other one, "Super Hummingbirds," also from Nature, and available on blu ray.
Loved the video.  Lots of different types of hummingbirds that are not seen in the us.
If you love watching nature stories and especially love watching humming birds...this is great...
Well, this is a Christmas gift for my youngest granddaughter who will love it when she opens it.

Stumbled across this looking for stocking stuffers.  Already a fan of the pbs nature productions, was glad to find this DVD. Stunning photography and fascinating facts make this a must for nature lovers.
